I dine in this restaurant quite a bit! This is my favorite spot to pass a nice evening.  I go to this spot routinely. The food is just great, the staff members are friendly and the cost is good. I enjoy being in this restaurant over a good supper.

This is hands down the best pizza I have ever tasted!  Normally, I'd go somewhere else, but thought, if people are waiting an hour to get pizza, it must be good. And boy am I glad we waited.

Very rude and poor customer service. I walked in and asked which types of pizza were in the window. The guy looks at me, rolls his eyes and asks, “what do you want?” - ignoring my question. When I point to a slice I think I want asking what it is, the same guy basically whispers what the pizza is - so I don't hear him. He places the pizza in the oven, and as I step aside to let the person behind me order, a new guys yells $3.50 miss at me.  I understand lunch is a busy time but there is no need for such rude service. The pizza was average and cold. I regret coming here and will definitely not the coming back or recommending it to others.

This is the real NYC pizza deal! Don’t even attempt to try the other pizza stores in the same neighborhood! Antonio’s pizza choices are classic for Brooklyn, square or regular. You’ll enjoy even the many choices that include plenty of toppings selection.  I loved every bite and I especially love their Sicilian square style pizza! Sauce was perfect.

Ladies and gents, it's all about the flavor!...We tried pizza all over the world (MIL) and trust me this is one of the best! Cheese or pepperoni, haven't tried anything else. This is the kind of place you buy a slice, walk a block then turn-around and buy another slice.

Amazing place! I had some stuff to do downtown and I saw this place.  I was thinking about it while doing my stuff. I stopped in on my way home and got a Personal pizza/regular with just cheese... It was amazing; tasty, hot, with lots of cheese & a perfect sauce. I ate it “al fresco” in a small park, ( Even though their seating area was good too), because I wanted to eat outside! The people there were helpful, knowledgeable, and friendly; Highly recommended!!! They put me in a great mood too!!!

I walked into here hoping for a welcoming experience and I received the worst service ever. Any establishment that makes a customer feel bad for wanting what they want has poor customer service. Sometimes I want fresh slices and they get mad at me for wanting it. There is one guy in particular who sometimes wears a fitted cap, when I asked him for my food he made a low comment that I couldn't really make out but as a customer it made me really uncomfortable. This is not the first time the service was terrible. Many of my coworkers felt terrible after coming to this location. Needless to say we will no longer bring our business to this pizza shop. I'll be going to another one.
